sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Parent Double Extension File Execution
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect execution of suspicious double extension files in ParentCommandLine

match_context.values: @{Hashes=SHA1=E563BAE25E3C011A1E69B4636C9B29B5661C460A,MD5=89B5A70BF37A93015F4845BF901B7825,SHA256=678652BB50ABB92DE91A69C05EA018C160FB4BE0902ACE14B15749246788CB40,IMPHASH=FD97AFEC4DC549DCD1FE1DAD15035DF9; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=Cmd.Exe; Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; Description=Windows Command Processor; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1635 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine="cmd.exe" /C "C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Local\Temp\qrzc3uqi.du5\CV.pdf.lnk"; CommandLine="C:\Windows\system32\cmd.exe" /c ftp.exe -s:"offsec-certified-professional.png"; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\cmd.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\cmd.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects encoded base64 MZ header in the commandline

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\system32\cmd.exe /C findstr /R TVqQAAMAAAAEAAAA//8AAL offsec-certified-professional.png > C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp && findstr /V /C:findstr /R C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp > %temp%\b64.tmp && move /Y %temp%\b64.tmp C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp >nul; Image=C:\Windows\system32\cmd.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potential Arbitrary Command Execution Via FTP.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects execution of "ftp.exe" script with the "-s" or "/s" flag and any child processes ran by "ftp.exe".

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Potentially Suspicious CMD Shell Output Redirect
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects inline Windows shell commands redirecting output via the ">" symbol to a suspicious location.
This technique is sometimes used by malicious actors in order to redirect the output of reconnaissance commands such as "hostname" and "dir" to files for future exfiltration.

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\system32\cmd.exe /C findstr /R TVqQAAMAAAAEAAAA//8AAL offsec-certified-professional.png > C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp && findstr /V /C:findstr /R C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp > %temp%\b64.tmp && move /Y %temp%\b64.tmp C:\ProgramData\b64.tmp >nul; Image=C:\Windows\system32\cmd.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious LNK Double Extension File Created
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of files with an "LNK" as a second extension. This is sometimes used by malware as a method to abuse the fact that Windows hides the "LNK" extension by default.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Copy From or To System Directory
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects a suspicious copy operation that tries to copy a program from system (System32, SysWOW64, WinSxS) directories to another on disk.
Often used to move LOLBINs such as 'certutil' or 'desktopimgdownldr' to a different location with a different name in order to bypass detections based on locations.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Markus Neis, Tim Shelton (HAWK.IO), Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
